British explorer Sir Ranulph Fiennes is to to lead the first team on foot across the Antarctic during the southern winter, he revealed today.

The 68-year-old will brave temperatures of minus 50C (minus 58F) during the expedition next year when his group will make the trip called the Coldest Journey On Earth. In some places temperatures are expected to be as low as -90C.

The team will carry out readings and measurements for scientists, 
providing data on marine life, oceanography and meteorology.

